5:
Sales are absolutely booming!
You're moving up in the world,
merchant man.
11:
At this rate, we'll be able to worm
our way into the Guild's inner circle!
Hehehehe! I can't wait!
15:
Um... Stinelle? I think... you've done
enough.
18: Huh? What are you on about?
22:
Thanks to you, those thugs have
backed off entirely, and my business
has grown exponentially.
24:
But... I'm really not worth all of this
effort.
27:
My ears must be malfunctioning...
What are you trying to say?
29:
This just isn't the shop I dreamed of.
Honestly... I don't know if the
customers are even happy.
31:
I'm going to sell the store and the
business to someone more capable.
I think that'll work best for everyone
involved.
32:
I'll use the money I get to start over
with a smaller shop. Thank you,
Stinelle, for getting me this far.
35:
Wait... That wasn't the plan. You can't
just...
39:
...Fine. Whatever. I should've known
better than to trust a
good-for-nothing like you to handle
such a complicated task.
41:
...So, that's it then. Our contract ends
here.
44: ...You're really fine leaving it like that?
46:
Yeah, well, you saw how upset he
was, didn't you? What else was I
supposed to do?
54: Mamas? What are you doing here?
58:
Your guard sent us a message
asking us to come get you.
61:
...Did something happen? You know
you can tell us whatever's on your
mind.
71: So he told you he'd had enough, huh?
75: Did I... mess up like last time?
80:
...You can't save someone who
doesn't want to be saved.
83:
Though the way I see it, you've
already done more than enough for
him.
86: Maybe we shouldn't have butted in...
89: So what if we did? I... I just...
92:
You just wanted him to be happy,
right?
95:
Don't worry... We know that's how
you really feel now, even if you do
go overboard sometimes.
98:
Kids make mistakes. It's a fact of life.
But what's important is the lessons
we learn from those mistakes. You
don't need me to tell you that, right?
102:
But what if it happens again? What
if... someone else says they don't
need me anymore?
106:
I've been thinking. What do YOU
want to do, Stinelle?
107:
You were so focused on that
merchant, but what about yourself?
111:
Isn't that obvious? I want to help
people.
115:
I used to be a god and will be again!
But if I can't help one helpless little
human, how can I save all of
humanity?!
118:
Emma, Luik... We're going to Nick's.
There's still more we can do.
132:
I... I want everyone under my watch
to be happy, but... I made a mistake.
136:
Just as those thugs tried to decide
your worth, so did I. I'm sorry.
139:
C-come now... You're not the one to
blame, Stinelle... I was just too weak...
141:
That may be so. Even for a human,
you're incompetent and outdated.
144:
Haven't you noticed? The people
who were going to buy this store
were scammers, just like the ones
from before.
149:
Nick realized it in time and
managed to stop the sale. You
ought to be on your hands and
knees thanking him, you know!
153:
*sigh* Well, you're only human, so I
guess these things are bound to
happen. Anyway, I've reconsidered a
few things...
156:
What's this... A list of companies...
and a list of buildings? What's this all
about?
158:
A list of prospective buyers for your
shop. And a list of potential new
storefronts, courtesy of Nick's father.
161: Why... would you do all of this for me?
163:
Let me ask you, merchant
manwhat do YOU want to do?
167:
I'm not going to make decisions for
you anymore. I just want to help you
find happiness.
170:
So, please... Tell us about your
dreams!
173:
You still came to my rescue, even
though I caused you trouble and
hurt your feelings...
175:
I'm sorry, and thank you. Can we...
work together to open up a new
shop?
179:
Of course! With me on your side,
you're guaranteed to be thrilled with
the results!
182:
I'm impressed at all the work you
put in, but... Aren't these prices a bit
high?
184:
That's what it takes to open a new
shop now. Honestly, how were you
expecting to run a business with
how little you charge?
186:
What?! That's how much it costs
now?!
188:
That's why my father decided it
wasn't worth trying to extort you...
192:
It's just like I've been saying all
along...
195:
Someone as incompetent as you
would never get anywhere on your
own! Count yourself lucky that we're
on your side!
